<br>
First let me explain the strategy for probably the two biggest questions. <br>
<br>
1) Spiroc isle and the warrior epic.<br>
Yes the Spiroc lord according to research is immidiate repop as long as the spiroc guardian or atleast one of the spirocs are still on the isle. We plan to leave the spiroc guardian as it doesn't move and shouldn't agro. We'll pull the lord away from his spawn spot kill him, hope for warrior epic drop. Wash rinse and repeat for a couple hours hopefully getting a good couple drops.<br>
<br>
***Yes we will have a botted camp out cleric.<br>
<br>
2) Bzzazzt isle. A pain in the rear. The plan is to send a break team in invis just as if we were doing Fear. Let them set up camp and one at a time send in a group invis'd. Should you get agro or invis wear off you are to just like fear stop, die and play dead. Once a camp established we'll pull the left bee, we'll probably get 2 adds. Chanters mezz the two adds we will 90% get. Upon killing the first bee it will split, the assistant tank take the add, his entire group and everyone else assists the MT/MA. Shaman of course slows the add and the main. This will then spawn another which clerics will chain heal the tank with the exception of the SA cleric. Wash and repeat for the split. Everyone camp out. Med, rebuff and take out the right bee...same sort of strategy though it is somewhat different on the split. Lastly the middle spawn, depending on how well we are doing we might take out the ending boss if we're not up to it we'll simply have someone kite it away from the camp, everyone camps out/or LD. clear agro split the &quot;PERTINANT&quot; loot and call it a day.<br>
<br>
** Camp out cleric provided<br>
**No sitting upon pull<br>
**Agro management...you get agro and not a MT plan on dieing.<br>
<br>
Lastly, I believe I hit all the epic mobs up to the seventh isle. This was done purposely so the Federation should not have to attend another POA raid for quite some time. If however I missed soemthing and you need it please letme know and I'll do my best to schedule it in. I think everyone is pretty much fed up with POA and hopefully this raid will take care of alot of people at once and allow the us not to have to go back up for quite some time. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uvilevilisto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VileVilisto</A> at: 8/8/02 5:31:06 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uvigdissangcarus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vigdis SangCarus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer of The Federation</span><br>  Posts: 320<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/8/02 5:08:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=122.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.unhomed.com/images/Sigs/PersonalIcon.gif height=96 width=59></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POA</span><hr size=1> <br>
